{"title":"New Limar Air Stratos road/gravel helmet is light, airy & affordable","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/01/limar-air-stratos-helmet/","date":1633099103000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/24113834/Limar-AirStratos-gravel-road-bike-helmet-2-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"new limar air stratos road bike helmet for gravel riding and more\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/24113834/Limar-AirStratos-gravel-road-bike-helmet-2-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/24113834/Limar-AirStratos-gravel-road-bike-helmet-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/24113834/Limar-AirStratos-gravel-road-bike-helmet-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/24113834/Limar-AirStratos-gravel-road-bike-helmet-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/24113834/Limar-AirStratos-gravel-road-bike-helmet-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/24113834/Limar-AirStratos-gravel-road-bike-helmet-2.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-272558\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Need a lightweight brain bucket for gravel and adventure rides? Check out <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2017/11/01/limars-new-ultralight-lux-adds-features-but-remains-one-of-the-lightest-helmets-in-the-world/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Limar</a>’s new Air Stratos helmet. &nbsp;A size medium tips the scale at a claimed 240g, and a size large weighs a reported ten grams more. But there’s more to it than just a low weight…</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/24113830/Limar-AirStratos-gravel-road-bike-helmet-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/24113830/Limar-AirStratos-gravel-road-bike-helmet-1.jpg\" alt=\"limar air stratos road and gravel bike helmet shown from all sides\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1178\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/24113830/Limar-AirStratos-gravel-road-bike-helmet-1.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/24113830/Limar-AirStratos-gravel-road-bike-helmet-1-297x219.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/24113830/Limar-AirStratos-gravel-road-bike-helmet-1-800x589.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/24113830/Limar-AirStratos-gravel-road-bike-helmet-1-120x88.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/24113830/Limar-AirStratos-gravel-road-bike-helmet-1-768x565.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/24113830/Limar-AirStratos-gravel-road-bike-helmet-1-1536x1131.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>It’s not the lightest helmet Limar’s ever made (that’s <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/15/limar-ultralight-evo-tweaks-worlds-lightest-bike-helmet-with-improved-durability/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">the Ultralight Evo</a>, which also happens to be one of the lightest in the world), but the Air Stratos is one of the lightest helmets with a $115 MSRP. And its 15 bigger vents and slightly deeper coverage make it a better all-around helmet for most roadies and gravel cyclists. It even gets non-allergenic pads inside. However, that light weight seems to come at the expense of additional safety systems as the helmet lacks MIPS or similar technologies. For a helmet that’s geared towards gravel, bikepacking, and adventure riding, that could be an important consideration.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/23135241/LIMAR_40711.jpg\" alt=\"limar air stratos\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/23135241/LIMAR_40711.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/23135241/LIMAR_40711-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/23135241/LIMAR_40711-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/23135241/LIMAR_40711-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/23135241/LIMAR_40711-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></p><p>The in-mold double-shell helmet comes in seven colors (white, black, blue, red, burgundy, gray, and army green), but only two sizes – Medium and Large.</p><p>It’s one entry of six in the brand’s new Air Revolution array, including designs built for everything from time trials to aero road racers to mixed-surface adventures.</p><p><a href=\"https://limar.com/air-revolution/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Limar.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Sam Anderson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"0f25c872e0d0ec3c33fdc5cd25c5deda3af5f2cdac60927c174a286467afa2a5","category":"Cycling"}